                            <td width="52%" class="copy"><p class="copyhead">Massage Therapy &amp; Spa Treatment</p>
                              <p>Make an appointment today and enjoy a session of massage therapy, specialty body treatments, or hot stone massage. We welcome our spa clients to use any part of the health club facility (pool, whirlpool, showers, steam room) for an additional charge of $5.<span class="sidebar_text"><a href="#spa"><br>
                                <br>
                                &raquo; Our Spa</a><br>
                                <a href="#massages">&raquo;  Massages</a><br>
                                <a href="#specialtymassages">&raquo;  Specialty Massages</a><br>
                                <a href="#specialtytreatments">&raquo;  Specialty Treatments</a><br>
                                <a href="#massagepackages">&raquo; Massage Packages</a><br>
                                <a href="#giftcertificates">&raquo; Git Certificates</a><br>
                                <a href="executive-health-club-spa-massage-policies.php">&raquo; Spa &amp; Message Therapy Policy</a></span>
                              <hr size="1" noshade color="#CCCCCC"><p><strong><a name="spa"></a></strong><span class="copyhead">Our Spa</span></p>
                              <p><strong>Our Therapist</strong><br>
                              Alice R. Huttick is a Licensed Massage Therapist. She is a graduate of The Swedish Institute in New York City where she studied Swedish, Shiatsu, Medical and Pre-Natal massage as well as Myofacial Release and Reflexology. Ms. Huttick has taken numerous classes at the Upledger Institute and specializes in Cranio Sacral and Somatic Emotional Release Therapy. She is a member of The Society of Ortho Bionomy Therapists and continues to take classes in Ortho Bionomy which includes Chapman's Reflexes. Ms. Huttick has taken numerous Spa Treatment courses at the Deroligica Institute and has extensive experience in various spa treatments.</p>
                              <p><strong>Appointments</strong><br>
                                We recommend that you book appointments in advance in order to receive your preferred date and time for your massage. We require a credit card at the time of booking in order to reserve the appointment. Any cancellations require six-hour notice to avoid a 50% charge. If you do not have a credit card, you are welcome to stop by and pay for your appointment in advance.</p>
                              <p><strong>Gratuities</strong><br>
                                If you are pleased with the services you have received, it is customary to give a 15% to 20% gratuity to your therapist.</p>
                              <p><strong>Age Requirement</strong><br>
                                Clients must be at least 18 years of age.</p>
                              <p><strong>Late Arrivals</strong><br>
                              We recommend that you arrive at least 5 minutes prior to your appointment. If you are late, we can offer you the time remaining on your treatment or gladly reschedule you for another day with a 50% charge for the missed appointment.</p>
                              <p><a href="spa-massage-policies.php" class="footnote">View our Spa &amp; Message Therapy Policy</a></p>
                              <a href="#top">&laquo; back to top</a>                              <hr size="1" noshade color="#CCCCCC">                              
                              <p><strong><a name="massages"></a></strong><span class="copyhead">Our Massages</span></p>
                              <p><strong>The following massages all share the same pricing</strong><br>
                                30 Minutes &ndash; $45<br>
                                45 Minutes &ndash; $55<br>
                                60 Minutes &ndash; $75<br>
                              90 Minutes &ndash; $115</p>
                              <p><strong>Swedish</strong><br>
                                This is a classic form of Western massage known for its use of long strokes, kneading, friction and stretching to reduce stress and relax muscles. It aides in muscles recovery from strains by releasing built up lactic and uric acid from muscle tissue. Swedish massage will relax, revitalize and renew your body.</p>
                              <p><strong>Neuromuscular/Deep Tissue</strong><br>
                                This massage uses steady, deep pressure on contracted areas to realign deeper layers of muscle and connective tissue (fascia). The therapist will work to release chronic muscle tension and restore fascia to its healthy state to achieve increased mobility and reduced pain. People suffering from problems such as chronic pain, repetitive 
                              strains or sprains, and muscle tension (including tension headaches) might find this type of massage particularly beneficial.</p>
                              <p><strong>Prenatal</strong><br>
                                Designed with the intention of relieving pain related to pregnancy, prenatal massage reduces sciatic nerve pain and aides in alleviating stress. It is popular for reducing 
                              back pain when medicinal choices may be limited. The expecting mother will lie on her side to provide safety and comfort to both her and her child. Prenatal massage is recommended after the first trimester of pregnancy.</p>
                              <p><strong>Reflexology</strong><br>
                                Reflexology is a foot massage that will serve as a tune-up for your entire body. The basis of this massage is a belief that contained within the feet is a complete map of the body&rsquo;s organs. By applying pressure to different areas on the soles of your feet a therapist is<br>
                              able to extend beneficial effects to different body parts.</p>
                              <p><strong>Reiki</strong><br>
                              A spiritual based practice that involves hand placement over and around the different chakras of the body to harmonize the mind with the body and allow for proper distribution of energy. Reiki massage can be used to send energy to broken bones to facilitate healing. This is a powerful and relaxing treatment for healing.</p>
                              <p><a href="#top">&laquo; back to top</a></p>
                              <hr size="1" noshade color="#CCCCCC">                              <p><strong><a name="specialtymassages"></a></strong><span class="copyhead">Our Specialty Massages</span></p>
                              <p><strong>Ortho Bionomy</strong> - $50 (30 min.) or $85 (60 min.)<br>
                                Developed by Dr. Arthur Lincoln Pauls, Ortho-bionomy seeks to create an understanding of the body. The therapist will work with the body instead of forcing change. Ortho-bionomy is used to relieve acute and chronic pain, patterns of chronic tension and stress. It is performed by placing the body and joints in positions of comfort then applying gentle motions and/or compression to result in less pain, reduced tension, greater circulation and flexibility. <em>Recipient will stay fully clothed for the duration of the session.</em></p>
                              <p><strong>Shiatsu</strong> - $50 (30 min.) or $85 (60 min.)<br>
                                Based on the Chinese meridian system, Shiatsu is an Eastern style of massage that uses strategic pressure from the palms and fingers of the therapist to disrupt energy blockages and restore chi to its optimal flow. This type of massage eases stress, improves circulation, and balances chi.</p>
                              <p><strong>Cranio Sacral</strong> - $50 (30 min.) or $85 (60 min.)<br>
                                This treatment uses a gentle touch to move the plates of the skull by working with the pulse of the craniosacral fluid to restore energy balance and relieve tension and stress. Healing is promoted from the inside out where the aim is a return to a more open, calm and graceful way of being. The recipient will stay fully clothed for the duration of the session.</p>
                              <p><strong>Hot Stone</strong> - $90 (60 min.)<br>
Heated, smoothed stones are used in combination with a traditional Swedish massage to provide a deeply relaxing experience. The heat of the stones can aid in the quick release of pressure from the muscles while soothing the body. Placement of stones on the body can help to increase energy flow.</p>
                              <p><strong>Chair Massage </strong> - $20 (15 min.)<br>
                                This is a fifteen minute Swedish massage that focuses on quickly relieving stress and tension by concentrating on the neck, shoulders and back. Chair massage is an ideal massage for a quick break from the office environment or a break from a day of conferences. The recipient will stay fully clothed for the duration of the session. </p>
                              <p><strong>Ask for information on bringing chair massage to your office or party!</strong></p>
                              <p><strong>Also available: </strong><br>
                              Thai Massage, Medical Massage, Myofascial Somato-Emotional Release,                              &amp; Chapman&rsquo;s Reflexes</p>
                              <p><a href="#top">&laquo; back to top</a></p>
                              <hr size="1" noshade color="#CCCCCC">
                              <p><strong><a name="specialtytreatments"></a></strong><span class="copyhead">Our Specialty Treatments </span></p>
                              <p><strong>Full Body Salt Glow </strong>- $125 (75 min.)<br>
                                Awaken your senses, stimulate your body and soften your skin with this natural
                                exfoliating treatment. Used in the Salt Glow is a unique blend of salts from the
                                Dead Sea and aromatherapy. This mixture stimulates your lymphatic system and
                                gently removes dead skin cells to improve skin texture; moisturizing lotion is them
                              applied to hydrate the skin.</p>
                              <p><strong>Shea Butter Body Treatment</strong> - $125 (75 min.)<br>
                                This rich treatment applied to the entire body will result in visible slimming and toning combined with unbelievable hydration. The process begins with a thermal grommage to stimulate and exfoliate the skin. It is followed with the heart of the treatment- a special massage cream enriched with honeysuckle and rosemary that provides enduring softness and moisture to thirsty skin. After the treatment the client walks away feeling refreshed and rejuvenated.</p>
                              <p><strong>Chocolate Decadence</strong> - $155 (90 min.)<br>
                                Created for the true chocolate lover, natural cocoa and sweet almond oil are used in a relaxing body treatment specifically designed to invigorate your senses and lift
                              your spirits. The client first receives a mild exfoliation to smooth the body and prepare the skin for the chocolate treatment. The heated chocolate and almond oil is rubbed into the skin to provide a unique form ofmoisture and relaxation. After a quick shower the treatment is finished with a soothing massage using a special chocolate massage cream.</p>
                              <p>Please add 7% New Jersey State Sales Tax to the price of all services.<br>
</p>
                              <hr size="1" noshade color="#CCCCCC">
                              <p><strong><a name="massagepackages" id="massagepackages"></a></strong><span class="copyhead">Massage Packages</span></p>
                              <ul>
                                <li>45 Minute Package &ndash; 7 Sessions for $350</li>
                                <li>60 Minute Package &ndash; 7 Sessions for $490</li>
                                <li>90 Minute Package &ndash; 7 Sessions for $770</li>
                              </ul>
                              <p>Note: The price list above does not include use of the Health Club facilities for non-members or sales tax. Non-members wishing to use the Health Club, add an additional $5 per session to the prices above. <strong>Hot Stone massages are an additional $15/60 min.</strong></p>
                              <p>Please add 7% New Jersey State Sales Tax to the price of all services.<br>
</p>
                              <hr size="1" noshade color="#CCCCCC">
                              <p><strong><a name="giftcertificates" id="massagepackages2"></a></strong><span class="copyhead">Gift Certificates</span></p>
                              <p>Gift Certificates may be purchased for Massages and Specialty Treatments. Gift Certificates may be upgraded to include Gratuity, use of the Health Club on the day of the massage, or both.</p>
                              <p><strong>Massage Gift Certificates<br>
                                </strong>These gift certificates may be upgraded to include gratuity, use of the Health Club on the day of the massage, or both. A Massage Gift Certificate may be redeemed for a Swedish, Neuromuscular/ Deep Tissue, Prenatal, Reflexology, or Reiki Massage.</p>
                              <ul>
                                <li>30 Minutes &ndash; $45 Massage Only / $53 with Gratuity </li>
                                <li>45 Minutes &ndash; $55 Massage Only / $65 with Gratuity</li>
                                <li>60 Minutes &ndash; $75 Massage Only / $89 with Gratuity</li>
